1
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:13,388
- Hey, Darla. How you doing today?
- Hey, Dan.

2
00:00:13,597 --> 00:00:18,310
- I'm looking for something in a Markowski.
- That'd be Dennis Markowski?

3
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,187
That's the one.

4
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:26,610
Oh, and I've got my paralegal
with me today.

5
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:29,029
Paralegal? Coming up in the world.

6
00:00:29,238 --> 00:00:30,739
You know it.

7
00:00:49,508 --> 00:00:51,093
Hey, Dennis.

8
00:00:51,677 --> 00:00:53,052
Have a seat.

9
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:20,163
You hear about Chow?

10
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:24,960
- Yeah, people say he skipped town.
- He's dead.

11
00:01:26,378 --> 00:01:27,462
It wasn't me.

12
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:30,299
It wasn't a message.
It wasn't payback.

13
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:34,386
It was a mistake made by a third party
who has since been dealt with.

14
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:35,679
You got it?

15
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:37,347
- Yeah.
- Second thing.

16
00:01:37,556 --> 00:01:40,601
The deal you had with Fring,
it's still in place.

17
00:01:40,809 --> 00:01:42,019
Okay.

18
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,812
Don't "okay" me.

19
00:01:44,021 --> 00:01:45,897
You got something to say?

20
00:01:47,733 --> 00:01:50,694
Mike, I'm keeping my mouth shut.

21
00:01:50,902 --> 00:01:52,654
The laundry was right above the lab.

22
00:01:52,738 --> 00:01:54,864
There's no way I could say
I wasn't in on it.

23
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:57,159
I'm looking at eight years minimum.

24
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:00,162
But I'm doing my time
like I'm supposed to.

25
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:02,289
I'm no rat, and you know it.

26
00:02:02,539 --> 00:02:04,541
I mean, what else is there to say?

27
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:07,043
All due respect,
what are we talking about here?

28
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,338
The deal is the deal.

29
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:15,093
How's the deal the deal?

30
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:17,471
The feds took away my hazard pay.

31
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:21,683
My wife asks me where the mortgage
is coming from. I got nothing to tell her.

32
00:02:21,892 --> 00:02:23,393
I knew the risks. We all did.

33
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:25,145
But that wasn't the deal.

34
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:28,231
And I know for a fact
they got Holt and Perez yesterday.

35
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:31,140
Now, it's not gonna be me,
but absent the hazard pay

36
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:34,529
- sooner or later, someone's gonna flip.
- No one's flipping.

37
00:02:34,738 --> 00:02:37,199
Everyone gets their hazard pay,
including you.

38
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:41,536
I appreciate what you're saying and all,
but the man is dead.

39
00:02:41,745 --> 00:02:43,955
Okay? The lab's a hole in the ground.

40
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,250
- I just don't see it.
- I've got something new.

41
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:50,379
It's just starting up.
It's gonna make you whole.

42
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:52,714
Something new?
With the feds looking at you?

43
00:02:52,798 --> 00:02:54,800
- How?
- "How" is my business.

44
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,052
Hanging tight's your business.

45
00:02:57,260 --> 00:03:01,431
Your family's gonna be fine.
You will be made whole.

46
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,684
Now, you got my word.

47
00:03:04,393 --> 00:03:05,811
You need more?

48
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:11,817
No, Mike. I'm good.

49
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:17,781
- Who's next?
- That's your choice.

50
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:20,867
A.P.D.'s got Martinez across town.
McGann's up in Sandoval.

51
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:23,620
The Sandia tribal cops
are holding him for the feds.

52
00:03:25,247 --> 00:03:27,874
And Holt and Perez
are in lockup in Los Lunas.

53
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:30,419
You don't mean to get to them all today?

54
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:32,254
Yeah, I do.

55
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:35,507
Hey, let's go! Open up!

56
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,636
{\an8}Back here.

57
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:43,784
{\an8}Oh, hi. How was your day?

58
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,413
{\an8}Are you moving back in?

59
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:51,958
{\an8}Yeah. I'll keep the condo for now.

60
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:54,628
{\an8}Selling it in this market,
I'd get killed.

61
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:58,089
{\an8}But, yeah, I'm home.

62
00:04:58,715 --> 00:04:59,800
{\an8}It's time.

63
00:05:03,053 --> 00:05:05,555
Do you really think that's a good idea?

64
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:08,683
{\an8}Yes.

65
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:38,588
{\an8}So you bring him here? Come on.

66
00:05:38,797 --> 00:05:40,797
The three of us, we're the three amigos.

67
00:05:40,966 --> 00:05:43,218
All for one, one for all.

68
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:46,054
{\an8}We don't need a fourth amigo.

69
00:05:46,263 --> 00:05:49,933
{\an8}Saul, Mike knows the business.
He knows distributors.

70
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:52,561
- Mike's okay.
- He's okay?

71
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,479
{\an8}He said he was gonna break my legs.

72
00:05:54,563 --> 00:05:57,023
{\an8}And don't tell me
he didn't mean it, okay?

73
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:59,932
{\an8}Because he gave me
the dead mackerel eyes. He meant it.

74
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:02,445
{\an8}Saul, Mike threatened me.
He threatened Jesse.

75
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:05,615
He probably threatened someone
before breakfast this morning.

76
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:08,702
It's what he does.
Come on. Grow a pair.

77
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:15,374
{\an8}Let it be noted
that I do this under duress.

78
00:06:15,584 --> 00:06:16,793
Duly noted.

79
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:21,631
{\an8}All right. Let him in, Huell.

80
00:06:34,853 --> 00:06:37,105
{\an8}Mike, I'm extending you...

81
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:41,943
{\an8}Now that we're all together,
here are the ground rules.

82
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:45,322
{\an8}Division of labor.
I handle the business.

83
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,949
{\an8}Making the stuff, that's your end.

84
00:06:48,407 --> 00:06:51,369
I don't tell you how to mix
your chemicals and whatnot,

85
00:06:51,578 --> 00:06:55,624
and you do not tell me
how to take care of business.

86
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:58,668
Is that absolutely clear?

87
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:08,053
{\an8}- Sure.
- All right. Let's take the tour.

88
00:07:12,182 --> 00:07:13,532
Hey, you're okay with that?

89
00:07:15,477 --> 00:07:16,519
Yes.

90
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:20,607
He handles the business,
and I handle him.

91
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:28,906
Clearly, we're talking
about renting, not buying.

92
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:31,826
{\an8}You need an ongoing business,
someplace you can slide in

93
00:07:31,910 --> 00:07:35,330
{\an8}do your thing and remain anonymous.
I'm not gonna mince words.

94
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:37,666
{\an8}This is your best bet.

95
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:42,170
{\an8}Got machines running, forklifts,
people coming and going.

96
00:07:42,379 --> 00:07:44,881
{\an8}You're gonna stay way under the radar.

97
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:48,635
{\an8}And the owner's solid. He can't
wait to throw up a curtain wall

98
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:51,929
{\an8}stack some boxes in front of it,
give you the space you need.

99
00:07:52,013 --> 00:07:54,640
{\an8}After that, he's got his business,
you've got yours,

100
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:56,434
{\an8}and never the twain shall meet.

101
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:58,728
It's outstanding. Am I right?

102
00:07:58,937 --> 00:08:01,773
Machines like this,
gotta be plenty of power.

103
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:03,191
What about the smell?

104
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,901
More good news.

105
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:08,321
I've been here when it's up and running.
This place stinks already.

106
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:10,573
{\an8}- You'll blend right in.
- How many employees?

107
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:11,741
{\an8}I knew you'd ask.

108
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:17,455
{\an8}Sixteen illegals, all highly motivated
to stay deaf, blind and dumb.

109
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,374
{\an8}You'll want to vet them, I'm sure.

110
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,751
{\an8}Yes, indeed.

111
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:23,878
{\an8}So, what do you say, maestro?

112
00:08:24,087 --> 00:08:25,714
{\an8}Is it unanimous?

113
00:08:25,922 --> 00:08:29,072
You know, I worked in a box factory
one summer in high school,

114
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:32,679
and I haven't seen one of these in years.

115
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,737
Trip down memory lane.
That's perfect.

116
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:36,224
You know what this is?

117
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:38,226
It's a corrugator.

118
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:42,272
It uses steam and salt to crimp
kraft paper for cardboard.

119
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:45,859
And it makes a hell of a racket doing it,
which is great. Right?

120
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:47,527
No.

121
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:49,779
Steam and salt.

122
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:53,074
When this thing is running,
it's like a jungle in here.

123
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:56,036
Shit. It'll ruin the product.

124
00:08:57,245 --> 00:09:02,083
You can't just pop down to Costco
and get a couple dehumidifiers?

125
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:06,212
What...? Fine. Fine. Moving on.

126
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:15,346
Spacious, isolated location, no humidity,

127
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:18,099
and you get all
the free tortillas you want.

128
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:20,560
That's the special feature of this place.

129
00:09:21,186 --> 00:09:22,771
I don't know.

130
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:25,231
It'll make the tortillas
smell like cat piss.

131
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,859
Somebody's bound to notice that.

132
00:09:28,068 --> 00:09:31,279
All right. Well, there's gotta be
some kind of workaround, right?

133
00:09:31,488 --> 00:09:34,115
It's a technical problem.
You guys are technical guys.

134
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:36,492
You know, be creative.
Put your heads together.

135
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:40,497
Anything food-related is gonna have
unannounced government inspections.

136
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:52,175
All I'm asking
is that you keep an open mind.

137
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:55,720
Danny's already set some space aside
behind the Skee-Ball games.

138
00:09:56,638 --> 00:09:59,599
- No.
- Hell, no.

139
00:10:07,982 --> 00:10:10,068
I know it's a long shot.

140
00:10:11,528 --> 00:10:13,279
{\an8}All I can say to recommend this

141
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:18,493
{\an8}is we're talking about an owner here who
is, how should I put it, highly amenable.

142
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:25,542
Look, I get it. Just say no
and we'll go get dinner.

143
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,961
All right. So I'll start.

144
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,838
No way we're cooking in here.

145
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:32,841
No space, nowhere for the smell to go.

146
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:36,594
Look at that door. That thing rolls up
and we're open to the world.

147
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:38,503
I don't know if anybody noticed,

148
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:41,057
but there's a cop shop
a quarter of a mile away.

149
00:10:41,141 --> 00:10:44,894
The hammer comes down,
it's gonna be Custer's Last Stand.

150
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:51,401
- It's perfect.
- What?

151
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:53,778
How are we gonna fit a lab in here?

152
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:57,157
Who said here?

153
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:14,840
A house is infested.

154
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:17,968
Termites, cockroaches, whatever.

155
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:21,430
Homeowners hire a pest control company.

156
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:24,683
Truck rolls up, homeowners leave.

157
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:26,810
The crew tents the house.

158
00:11:27,018 --> 00:11:29,480
They bomb the place with poison.

159
00:11:29,688 --> 00:11:31,524
The house stays like that for days.

160
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:33,943
No one looks twice at a tented house.

161
00:11:34,151 --> 00:11:36,653
Now, maybe there's a strange smell
coming out of it.

162
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:38,637
Does someone think to investigate? No.

163
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:42,033
Does anyone go inside? Hell, no.

164
00:11:45,036 --> 00:11:46,914
And that's where we'll cook.

165
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:52,711
They tent, what,
three, four houses a week?

166
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:55,172
So we pick the one that's best for us.

167
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,383
Enough floor space, easy access.

168
00:11:57,591 --> 00:12:01,136
Once the tent is up,
we go in, we cook a batch

169
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:04,473
we bomb the place and leave.

170
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:07,935
So we gotta move
in and out for every cook?

171
00:12:08,143 --> 00:12:11,772
Set up a lab, cook,
and then take everything down?

172
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:15,109
It's challenging, but doable.

173
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:18,487
Tell me about these guys.

174
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:24,159
Mr. Ponytail on the sidewalk, that's Ira.
He's the owner. On the roof is Sandor.

175
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:27,246
The ladder's Fernando,
and down below, that's Todd.

176
00:12:27,454 --> 00:12:31,249
The pest control operation is legit.
I mean, they're licensed, they're bonded.

177
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,627
They do as good a job as anyone in town.

178
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:36,547
But they're also top-drawer
second-story men.

179
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:39,758
- "Second-story"?
- B and E artists.

180
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,885
They're burglars.

181
00:12:42,093 --> 00:12:43,993
Yeah. I mean, hey, they play it smart.

182
00:12:44,095 --> 00:12:46,556
They don't boost anything
while they're on the job.

183
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:49,852
They copy the keys,
locate the valuables and alarms,

184
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:54,273
and they sell that information to other
crews. Or, after a decent interval

185
00:12:54,481 --> 00:12:58,027
- they'll lift the goods themselves.
- And you know them how?

186
00:12:58,235 --> 00:13:03,407
Oh, I've been pulling their chestnuts out of
the fire, legally speaking, for five years.

187
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:07,202
Ira and his guys are good. I mean,
they know how to keep their mouths shut.

188
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:09,579
And if you buy them,
they're gonna stay bought.

189
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:11,665
You can check into them yourself.

190
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:15,294
I will, if it comes to that.

191
00:13:15,502 --> 00:13:18,297
So do we take a vote?

192
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:22,426
Why?

193
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:03,174
- We sound great.
- Rock on, man. Solid.

194
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,761
That Yamaha's got a real nice touch.

195
00:14:05,969 --> 00:14:08,472
You like the sound? It's huge, huh?

196
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:11,808
Yeah, it's real nice, but we're looking
for something else today.

197
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:14,185
- You got any roadie cases?
- For sure. What size?

198
00:14:14,269 --> 00:14:15,646
Biggest you got.

199
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:18,304
That'll fit through, like,
a regular-size doorway.

200
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,067
You got it. Follow me.

201
00:14:23,278 --> 00:14:24,905
Top of the line.

202
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:28,659
Recessed hardware, foam lining,
quarter-inch laminated walls

203
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:30,661
3-inch casters.

204
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:34,998
Height is good, width is good.
How much weight will this hold?

205
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:36,959
It's rated for 900 pounds.

206
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:40,254
So unless your band plays lead bricks,
you should be okay.

207
00:14:42,631 --> 00:14:44,425
We're gonna need...

208
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:47,636
Hey, man, I'm trying to do business
over here, bitch.

209
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,848
Sorry. He's, like, overly enthusiastic.

210
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:54,268
Anyway, I'm gonna need four of them.

211
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:58,176
Four? That gonna be layaway? Because
I need to see a bunch of IDs for that.

212
00:14:58,272 --> 00:14:59,940
No, man, cash.

213
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:01,817
Okay. Hey, you know what?

214
00:15:02,025 --> 00:15:05,154
I'll throw in stenciling.
What's your band called?

215
00:15:15,205 --> 00:15:17,666
Damn, brother.

216
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:21,378
Not asking no questions, but it sure
looks like you're back in business.

217
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:23,922
No joke.
You way back in business, man.

218
00:15:24,131 --> 00:15:25,632
Look at this.

219
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:27,676
Yeah.

220
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:32,138
You're stacking the benjies
till the rubber band pops.

221
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:33,432
Yeah, yeah.

222
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:36,351
All's we're saying is
we know you're major league now,

223
00:15:36,435 --> 00:15:38,937
but if there's ever anything else
you need from us...

224
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:41,440
Any way we can get in on this at all.

225
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:43,942
Little stuff, big stuff...

226
00:15:44,151 --> 00:15:46,236
We would be all over it.

227
00:15:48,363 --> 00:15:51,200
You know, maybe someday.

228
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:57,623
That's cool.
I guess we better hit it then.

229
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:59,750
Yeah. Keep on keeping on, brother.

230
00:15:59,958 --> 00:16:01,251
Later.

231
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:06,757
<i>Okay, it is the same job as always.</i>

232
00:16:06,965 --> 00:16:10,552
You go out, you inspect, you deal
with the customers, regular drill.

233
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:15,182
Everything's the same,
except for one important detail.

234
00:16:21,688 --> 00:16:23,857
- No stealing.
- No stealing.

235
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:27,277
Not a toothpick, not the spare change
between the couch cushions

236
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:30,611
not the panties out of the hamper.
Nothing. And I mean nothing.

237
00:16:30,697 --> 00:16:34,576
If you're out with your buddies and they
ask if you got a hot tip on a B and E

238
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,287
you tell them you got nada.
You're out of the game.

239
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:41,291
The bottom line is that these houses
