- This is it.
- Wait. Wait for it.

495
00:38:07,744 --> 00:38:10,580
- Ready?
- <i>You wanna play rough? Okay!</i>

496
00:38:10,788 --> 00:38:14,250
- <i>Say hello to my little friend!</i>
- "Say hello to my little friend."

497
00:38:14,959 --> 00:38:17,170
Nice. Just...

498
00:38:17,378 --> 00:38:20,173
Hey, Mom, feeling better?

499
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:23,031
Hey. Hey, why don't you join us,
if you feel up to it?

500
00:38:23,176 --> 00:38:25,762
We have popcorn.
I think there's some pizza left.

501
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:27,555
If you're up to it.

502
00:38:27,764 --> 00:38:30,141
Yeah, Mom. Join us.

503
00:38:32,602 --> 00:38:34,520
- Oh, my God. Look. Look.
- <i>You whores!</i>

504
00:38:36,773 --> 00:38:38,773
Everyone dies in this movie, don't they?

505
00:38:50,369 --> 00:38:52,205
Okay.

506
00:38:52,413 --> 00:38:54,081
For you and you and me.

507
00:38:54,290 --> 00:38:57,293
Three hundred and sixty-seven thousand
dollars each.

508
00:38:57,502 --> 00:38:59,504
Wait a minute.

509
00:38:59,712 --> 00:39:01,506
After the dealers got their cut

510
00:39:01,714 --> 00:39:08,221
we should be looking at 1,379,560.

511
00:39:09,305 --> 00:39:10,890
Mike, you're short.

512
00:39:11,098 --> 00:39:12,975
You're almost 300,000 short.

513
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:16,234
You're forgetting about the mules.
They get a flat 20 percent.

514
00:39:16,395 --> 00:39:17,688
- The what?
- The drivers.

515
00:39:17,897 --> 00:39:21,234
They're the ones that take the product
from us to the dealers.

516
00:39:22,443 --> 00:39:27,156
And so transportation
is worth 20 percent?

517
00:39:27,365 --> 00:39:29,325
They're taking a risk.

518
00:39:30,660 --> 00:39:34,497
Two hundred and seventy-five thousand
dollars' worth of risk?

519
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:40,294
What did Gus pay his mules?

520
00:39:40,503 --> 00:39:43,005
Gustavo Fring didn't use mules.

521
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:44,423
He didn't need them.

522
00:39:44,632 --> 00:39:47,593
He spent 20 years
building his own distribution.

523
00:39:47,802 --> 00:39:51,013
He had 16 refrigerator trucks
running his product.

524
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:53,349
And do you know where they are now?

525
00:39:53,558 --> 00:39:55,226
Government impound.

526
00:39:55,434 --> 00:39:58,979
You don't like paying 20 percent?
Maybe you shouldn't have killed the guy.

527
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:02,024
Hey, hey. There's still over
a million bucks here, all right?

528
00:40:02,108 --> 00:40:04,151
That's for one cook.

529
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:06,737
And since you're putting on
the green eyeshade

530
00:40:06,821 --> 00:40:08,990
my supplier and I came to an agreement.

531
00:40:09,198 --> 00:40:11,284
The methylamine is free this time.

532
00:40:11,492 --> 00:40:15,621
But brace yourself, because
the next barrel is gonna cost big.

533
00:40:17,123 --> 00:40:20,209
Can we continue, or you got any more
burning questions?

534
00:40:23,379 --> 00:40:24,714
Okay, kid.

535
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:27,466
You fronted us 120 to get us going.

536
00:40:28,384 --> 00:40:33,180
So that's 40 from him and me.

537
00:40:33,389 --> 00:40:35,266
One hundred and twenty.

538
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:37,310
Yes. Thank you, Jesse.

539
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:39,520
Okay.

540
00:40:39,729 --> 00:40:43,691
Now, Ira gets 110
for our piece of the business,

541
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:46,068
and 25 per cook.

542
00:40:46,694 --> 00:40:49,155
That is 45

543
00:40:49,655 --> 00:40:51,824
from each of us.

544
00:40:57,496 --> 00:41:00,875
Ira's guys get 10 each per cook.

545
00:41:06,839 --> 00:41:10,843
Goodman's cut, 18,000 from each.

546
00:41:19,393 --> 00:41:23,230
Legacy cost, $351,000.

547
00:41:23,439 --> 00:41:25,274
That's 117,000 each.

548
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:26,984
"Legacy cost"?

549
00:41:27,193 --> 00:41:28,778
I got nine guys.

550
00:41:28,986 --> 00:41:32,239
You don't know them, but they were
part of the previous operation,

551
00:41:32,323 --> 00:41:35,534
and they know a lot.
And right now, some of them are in jail,

552
00:41:35,618 --> 00:41:39,205
and more will be soon.
The feds RICO-ed their hazard pay.

553
00:41:39,413 --> 00:41:42,792
So we are gonna make them whole.

554
00:41:43,709 --> 00:41:45,753
We are gonna make them whole?

555
00:41:45,962 --> 00:41:47,546
What is this "we"?

556
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:50,132
These were Gus' employees, not ours.

557
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:53,636
They might have been Gus' employees,
but they're my guys.

558
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:58,265
So, what are they doing
to further our interests?

559
00:41:58,474 --> 00:42:01,560
The cops are looking at them
very closely.

560
00:42:01,769 --> 00:42:05,064
We don't want them
furthering our interests.

561
00:42:05,272 --> 00:42:08,776
So we are paying them, why?

562
00:42:08,985 --> 00:42:13,072
Because it's what you do.

563
00:42:15,282 --> 00:42:17,535
It's what you do.

564
00:42:19,912 --> 00:42:22,832
My guys are keeping their mouths shut.

565
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,500
We make them whole.

566
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:28,462
One hand washes the other.
It's as simple as that.

567
00:42:29,296 --> 00:42:31,298
It sounds like a simple shakedown

568
00:42:31,507 --> 00:42:33,551
simple as that.

569
00:42:33,759 --> 00:42:36,762
We're paying for their silence.
That's blackmail.

570
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:40,641
Business is my end.

571
00:42:41,934 --> 00:42:44,228
This is business. End of story.

572
00:42:46,814 --> 00:42:50,192
This is your problem.
It should come out of your end.

573
00:42:50,401 --> 00:42:53,154
Hey. Hey. Just take it out of mine.

574
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,407
All right? Go for it.

575
00:42:57,158 --> 00:42:59,160
I don't care. Just take it.

576
00:43:08,836 --> 00:43:11,338
No. Jesse, thank you,

577
00:43:11,547 --> 00:43:13,674
but no.

578
00:43:13,883 --> 00:43:15,342
I'll pay my share.

579
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:17,928
Go ahead.

580
00:43:24,060 --> 00:43:25,853
Let me tell you something.

581
00:43:28,147 --> 00:43:29,523
This

582
00:43:30,858 --> 00:43:35,071
is how it's gonna be from here on out.

583
00:43:35,696 --> 00:43:39,742
My guys are an ongoing expenditure,

584
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:43,245
so you best get yourself
comfortable with it.

585
00:43:53,255 --> 00:43:55,508
A hundred and thirty-seven thousand.

586
00:43:58,844 --> 00:44:00,888
That's less than with Fring.

587
00:44:02,181 --> 00:44:06,519
Listen, Walter.
Just because you shot Jesse James

588
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:10,106
don't make you Jesse James.

589
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:19,115
Tomorrow.

590
00:44:34,922 --> 00:44:36,757
How are you feeling?

591
00:44:37,466 --> 00:44:38,676
Okay, I guess.

592
00:44:40,719 --> 00:44:42,513
Broke it off with Andrea.

593
00:44:43,264 --> 00:44:44,890
I had to.

594
00:44:45,808 --> 00:44:47,351
She's gonna tell Brock.

595
00:44:49,854 --> 00:44:52,147
I'm still gonna take care
of the rent and stuff.

596
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:55,943
- It's the right thing to do, but, you know...
- I meant this.

597
00:44:56,152 --> 00:44:58,362
How are you feeling about the money?

598
00:45:00,030 --> 00:45:02,630
You're looking at it wrong.
When we worked for Gus

599
00:45:02,741 --> 00:45:05,035
we were cooking 200 pounds a week.

600
00:45:05,244 --> 00:45:09,664
This last batch was great,
but we didn't even crack 50 pounds.

601
00:45:09,874 --> 00:45:13,294
We maybe cleared less money,
but we got a bigger piece of the pie.

602
00:45:14,170 --> 00:45:18,632
It's like you said, we're owners,
not employees.

603
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:24,388
I've been thinking about Victor.

604
00:45:25,431 --> 00:45:26,724
Yeah?

605
00:45:27,516 --> 00:45:28,934
Yeah.

606
00:45:29,810 --> 00:45:32,104
All this time

607
00:45:32,313 --> 00:45:35,441
I was sure that Gus did what he did

608
00:45:35,649 --> 00:45:37,526
to send me a message.

609
00:45:39,862 --> 00:45:42,072
Maybe there's another reason.

610
00:45:42,656 --> 00:45:44,575
Like what?

611
00:45:47,036 --> 00:45:49,914
Victor trying to cook
that batch on his own?

612
00:45:50,122 --> 00:45:52,374
Taking liberties
that weren't his to take?

613
00:45:54,752 --> 00:45:57,588
Maybe he flew too close to the sun

614
00:45:58,589 --> 00:46:00,299
got his throat cut.

